  "datePublished": "2025-10-02",
  "description": "tilepy is an open-source Python package for scheduling follow-up observations of multi-messenger transient events with large sky localization uncertainties, such as gravitational waves, gamma-ray bursts, and high-energy neutrinos. It supports 2D and 3D (galaxy-catalog-based) tiling strategies and is accessible via a public API and through the Astro-COLIBRI platform.",
